Atlanta Startup Jobs | VP of Product Management
 Toggle navigationAtlanta Startup Jobs HOME CONTACT RESOURCES REMOTE JOBSJob AlertsBackVP of Product ManagementLUMA, Home Inc.Startup Location: Atlanta, GA
Luma, Home Inc. – Vice President of Product Management
With the rise of the connected home, people are using more devices than ever. Home WiFi networks now need to be able to keep every one of them running and fully secure. The team at Luma Home has decided to use their expertise to create the perfect, personalized WiFi network for everyone.  Luma’s mission is clear: to deliver to each customer’s home the fastest, simplest, most secure, and most reliable home network that’s equipped for the technology of today, and tomorrow.  You can learn more about us at www.getluma.com.    
MAIN ROLE RESPONSIBILITIES:

Strategically advise and collaborate with the executive team on the vision of the product and the company.  Be exceptionally product-minded (constantly thinking of innovation and improvements from customers’ perspective.) 
Own the full product management lifecycle – gathering requirements from a broad spectrum of stakeholders.  Internally working closely with engineering, marketing, and sales, and externally working with customers, analysts, domain thought leaders, and continually accessing competitive capabilities.   
Writing detailed product requirements that clearly define the features to be developed by the engineering team and ensuring that the delivered product meets the needs of customers.
While the role will have an external/evangelical component, it will be more focused on defining and executing the product roadmap. 
Have the vision/capability to help the company transition from a one product/one market organization to a multi-product/multi-market company. 
Help to identify future investment and market opportunity.
Establish discipline around requirements gathering, product prioritization, schedules/deadlines, output and requests

 DESIRED SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE:   

Proven success in a fast-paced, start-up environment with a hands-on, “roll up your sleeves and grind it” approach. 
Prior experience managing a team across multiple product lines.
Hands-on experience being able to effectively interact with multiple constituencies including Engineering, Marketing, Sales, and external customers.
Expertise in product home connected market 
Hands-on experience managing, building and motivating a world-class global Product Management organization. Experience leading a business team successfully through rapid product proliferation and market platform expansion. 
Rigorous product management background, with rich experience managing product roadmaps and defining product prioritization based on business goals.
Capacity to bring positive energy and enthusiasm to a team and help the product management team establish credibility within the broader organization. 
Experience managing release schedules in the context of an agile development environment.
Bachelor’s Degree in a technical field.

 PERSONAL QUALIFICATIONS:

Strategic/big thinker and visionary who can create and develop the long-term product vision.
Willing to work directly with a small, fast-moving, smart team and able to work in ambiguous and rapidly-changing growth environment.
Smart, collaborative and able to communicate clearly.  Looks to “seek the truth.”  Not a pontificator.  Talks through difficult issues with colleagues and make decisions based on evidence and argument, not ego. 
Decisive in complex business situations.  Cool under pressure.  Has sufficient maturity and experience to recognize and react quickly to unexpected opportunities and challenges.
A results-oriented, motivating leader who can lead teams, positively influence peers and superiors and deliver great products and outcomes. Can motivate, persuade and challenge subordinates and peers to achieve desired results. Can balance the use of deadlines, accountability and positive reinforcement for superlative team performance.
Metrics-driven. Able to translate strategy into measurable operational goals and objectives. Disciplined in assessing performance and addressing problems. Rigorous in delivering results, and in holding team members accountable for their own results.
Highest ethics, integrity and intellectual honesty. Possesses a strong sense of self-confidence and unquestioned integrity with a strong sense of personal ownership and responsibility in accomplishing the company’s product and overall vision and goals.

Luma is committed to building a strong team that is connected to and helps strengthen the culture of our company. We have a cool headquarters in midtown Atlanta located in a great central location.  We offer a competitive total pay package which includes stock options, discounted health benefits, paid holidays and vacation, and more!       
Luma is Surround WiFi that brings home internet into the modern era. With a focus on speed, safety and security, Luma empowers users with visibility into their home WiFi system and control over their family and home network’s safety. You’ve never had WiFi like this.

To apply for this job email your details to [email protected]

